The '''Love Pier''' ({{zh|c=真愛碼頭|p=Zhēn'ài Mǎtóu|poj=Chin-ài Bé-thâu}}) is a [[pier]] along [[Love River]] in [[Yancheng District, Kaohsiung|Yancheng District]], [[Kaohsiung]], [[Taiwan]]. It is one of the most famous place to enjoy the seaside and scenery of the river with Kaohsiung skyline.<ref name="taiwan1">{{cite web|url=http://eng.taiwan.net.tw/pda/m1.aspx?sNo=0002121&id=A12-00075 |title=Welcome to Taiwan True Love Pier |publisher=Eng.taiwan.net.tw |date= |accessdate=2014-04-30}}</ref>

==History==
The pier area used to be the No. 12 dock of the [[Republic of China Armed Forces]].<ref>{{cite web|author=River Hotel Chain |url=http://www.riverhotel.com.tw/main-attractions-es.html |title=Welcome to the city Kaohsiung of Taiwan - Main Attractions |publisher=Riverhotel.com.tw |date= |accessdate=2014-04-30}}</ref>

==Features==
[[File:Windsurfing of Love Pier in Kaohsiung, Taiwan.JPG|thumb|Love Pier double sail]]
The pier is famous for its double sail design.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kcs.kcg.gov.tw/new_kcb/turelove-pier_en.php |title=Kaohsiung City Shipping Co., Ltd.- Love Pier |publisher=Kcs.kcg.gov.tw |date= |accessdate=2014-04-30}}</ref> It also houses the ''South District Police Department'' movie set building, made for the Taiwanese series [[Black & White (TV series)|Black and White]].<ref>{{cite web|author=Gwendolyn Ng |url=http://www.relax.com.sg/print/article/features/kaohsiung-shines-in-black-and-white |title=Kaohsiung shines in Black And White |publisher=Relax.com.sg |date=2012-05-28 |accessdate=2014-04-30}}</ref>

==Transportation==
The pier is accessible within walking distance East from [[Yanchengpu metro station|Yanchengpu Station]] of [[Kaohsiung MRT]].<ref name="taiwan1"/>

==Popular culture==
* [[Black & White (TV series)|Black and White]]
* [[Hi My Sweetheart]]<ref>{{cite web|author=Operating hours Tue - Sun: 6.30pm - 8.10pm |url=http://qiito.com/place/59-true-love-ferry-pier |title=True Love Ferry Pier - Pier in Taiwan |publisher=Qiito |date= |accessdate=2014-04-30}}</ref>

